						<block class="mm_flexcontainer mm_flexboxSet3">
							<block class="mm_exerciseColumn1">
								<h3>Moonbows</h3>
								<p>Did you know that rainbows can happen at night? They’re called moonbows. Look for them when the moon is very bright and it’s raining. They’re really beautiful.</p>
								<image src="p052a.png" title=""/>
							</block>
							<block class="mm_exerciseColumn2">
								<image src="p052b.png" title=""/>
								<h3>Contrails</h3>
								<p>When planes fly, they sometimes make long white marks called contrails. This happens because the hot air from the plane changes to water and ice when it meets the cold sky.</p>
							</block>
							<block class="mm_exerciseColumn3">
								<h3>Sun dogs</h3>
								<p>When there’s ice in the atmosphere, you can see sun dogs. Sun dogs are pairs of bright spots that appear on a ring around the Sun. You see them all over the world and in any season.</p>
								<image src="p052c.png" title=""/>
							</block>
						</block>

